To differentiate \(y=\sin^{-1}(x^2)\), set \(u=x^2\).  Then by the chain rule,

\[
\frac{dy}{dx}
=\frac{d}{du}\bigl(\sin^{-1}u\bigr)\cdot\frac{du}{dx}
=\frac{1}{\sqrt{1-u^2}}\cdot(2x)
=\frac{2x}{\sqrt{1-(x^2)^2}}
=\frac{2x}{\sqrt{1-x^4}}\,.
\]

Hence
\[
\boxed{\frac{dy}{dx}=\frac{2x}{\sqrt{1-x^4}}\,.}
\]
